<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,404,429]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Hosts.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[279,472,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Houghia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confinis">
<emphasis box="[279,472,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Houghia confinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reared 
<number box="[659,687,404,428]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" value="17.0">17</number>
times, and entirely from a sample of 
<number box="[1102,1159,404,428]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" value="3000.0">3000</number>
+ grass-eating butterflies (
<taxonomicName box="[158,313,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nymphalidae</taxonomicName>
) belonging to seven genera that eat only 
<taxonomicName box="[773,868,440,463]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, except for a single additional rearing from a wildcaught pupa of an unknown (and unknowable) species of hesperiine skipper butterfly (
<taxonomicName box="[1165,1306,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
). However, there also remains the possibility that what was identified as a hesperiine pupa might have been actually a nymphalid butterfly pupa.
</paragraph>
